[[John Searle]] used the notion of "direction of fit" to create a taxonomy of [[illocutionary act]]s.
<ref>[[John Searle]] (1975) "A Taxonomy of Illocutionary Acts", in: Gunderson, K. (ed.), ''Language, Mind, and Knowledge'' (Minneapolis: University of Minnesota Press) pp. 344-369.</ref>
<ref>[[John Searle]] (1976) "A Classification of Illocutionary Acts", ''Language in Society'', Vol.5,  pp. 1-24.</ref>
